==English==

===Etymology===
Biblical: Judas betraying Jesus with a kiss.

===Noun===
'''the kiss of death''' {{idiom}}

# A [[kiss]] on the [[cheek]] that signifies the [[death]] of the receiver, as delivered by [[mob boss]] or one with such influence.
#(''informal'') Something that may seem good and [[favourable]] but that actually brings [[ruin]] to hopes, plans, etc. 
#:'' The role in the soap opera was '''the kiss of death''' for Ann's career as a theatrical actress.''

